Overview
This module introduced proactive threat hunting — going beyond reactive alert triage to actively search for 
hidden threats within an environment. Unlike traditional monitoring which waits for alerts to fire, threat hunting starts with a 
hypothesis and searches for evidence to confirm or deny it.

Key Concepts Covered

Understanding the threat hunting lifecycle
Developing hypotheses based on threat intelligence and the MITRE ATT&CK framework
Using SIEM data to proactively search for attacker TTPs
Identifying low-and-slow attacks that evade signature-based detection
Documenting hunt findings and converting successful hunts into detection rules


Threat Hunting Lifecycle

Hypothesis — Form a question based on threat intel or ATT&CK techniques
Investigation — Query SIEM/log data to look for evidence
Discovery — Identify suspicious patterns or anomalies
Response — Escalate confirmed findings, contain if active
Improvement — Convert successful hunts into automated detections


