Key Takeaways
Threat hunting requires a different mindset than alert triage. Rather than reacting to what the SIEM surfaces,
you are actively looking for what it might be missing. The most valuable hunts often uncover attacker activity that has been 
present for days or weeks without triggering a single alert.
The MITRE ATT&CK framework is an invaluable reference for structuring hunts — starting with a specific technique and working
backwards from what artifacts it would leave behind is an effective approach.
